\n< Guild Master>So you failed to collect the goblin
noses.

\n< Serena>I never liked the idea in the first
place.

\n< Serena>Even if it's to confirm the
extermination, carrying back parts of a
corpse...
\n< Serena>It's just too barbaric.
\n< Guild Master>The opponent is a monster, you know?
\n< Serena>That's exactly why.

That's exactly why we, as bearers of
civilization and guardians of culture,
must demonstrate our pride to those
monsters.\n< Serena>
Isn't that right?\n< Serena>
\n< Guild Master>...

\n< Guild Master>Well... you're free to stick to your
principles.

Anyway, it's about the agreement. The
contract was for 10 goblin noses at 3G
each, right?\n< Guild Master>

\n< Guild Master>Since you brought back zero, your reward
is also zero.

Hmph. Well, it was my choice. I have no
objections. I wasn't counting on the
reward anyway.\n< Serena>

But, after all is said and done, I did
carry out the extermination and even
saved some people in the process.\n< Serena>

Make sure to record the fact that the
request was carried out in the history.\n< Serena>

\n< Guild Master>Right. Normally, this would be recorded
as a failure...

But since there are witnesses this time,
let's mark it as a success. This is
truly unprecedented. A successful
request without a reward.\n< Guild Master>

\n< Serena>I need \V[2501] more requests to fulfill
our agreement.

After a few more requests, you'll issue
me a pass\n< Serena>\V[2501]After a few more requests, you'll issue me a pass
\n< Serena>Is that correct?

\n< Guild Master>That's right. How many times have we
gone over this...?

\n< Serena>I'm in a hurry. No matter how many times
we confirm it, it's never enough.
\n< Serena>Just \V[2501] more requests...
\n< Guild Master>And take this with you.
\n< Serena>What's this?

It's issued to adventurers after their
first job... well, it's an ID of sorts.\n< Guild Master>

Achievements and evaluations are also
recorded here. Don't lose it.\n< Guild Master>

\n< Serena>A proof of being a full-fledged
adventurer, then. Understood.
\n< Serena>Now then.

That's enough for today. I need to take
care of myself for tomorrow.\n< Serena>
\n< Serena>Eat, take a bath, and sleep.

Oh yes, I also need a replacement ring.
Without it, I can't unleash my Sonic
Fist.\n< Serena>

Really, being an adventurer is
unexpectedly busy work.\n< Serena>

For starters, I should secure lodging.
Everything else comes after that.\n< Serena>
依頼開始

\n< Guild Master>Hey there, good morning. Have you gotten
used to this town yet?

\n< Serena>It's only been a day since yesterday. I
haven't had time to get used to it or
not.
\n< Guild Master>Heh, that's true.
\n< Serena>I'd like to see the quests.
依頼　序盤

\n< Guild Master>You haven't finished the request yet,
have you? Come back after you've
completed it.

\n< Serena>Waitress? What kind of request is this?

\n< Guild Master>Hey, hey, you don't seem like you've
been... to a tavern, have you?

\n< Serena>I did enter a tavern recently. I didn't
stay long, though.

\n< Guild Master>I see... Well, there's no need for it...
at your age, not yet...

\n< Guild Master>If you don't know how things work, it
might not be the right job for you,
young lady.

\n< Guild Master>Basically, you take orders from
customers and carry drinks and food to
the table. It's a request to help out at
the shop.

\n< Serena>You want me to pretend to be a waitress?
Me?

\n< Guild Master>No one's asking you to do it if you
don't like it. You don't have to do it
if you don't want to.

\n< Serena>Hmm. But it does sound interesting. It's
a job I'd likely never encounter if I
stayed in the mansion all my life.

\n< Serena>Besides... yes, those frilly clothes...
they are somewhat... nice... Can I wear
those clothes?

\n< Guild Master>I don't know which clothes you're
talking about, but I think you'll be
given a uniform. Whether they have one
in your size, I can't say...

\n< Guild Master>By the way, the payment is commission-
based. How much you earn is up to you.
I'll take it
I won't accept it
請ける

\n< Serena>Very well. I accept this request.
Contact the client.

\n< Guild Master>Then take this paper with you as is.
That will get the conversation going.
\n< Serena>I see. Then I'll be going.
\n< Guild Master>Ah- take care now-.

\n< Guild Master>...damn, I got carried away. Felt like
sending my daughter on an errand for the
first time.

\n< Serena>Assistance for a farmer?

\n< Guild Master>What, are you interested in that kind of
work?

\n< Serena>It's not about interest; the description
is too vague to understand what's
required.
\n< Serena>What kind of request is this?
\n< Guild Master>Uh, this time it's... milking cows.

\n< Guild Master>Farmers are always short on hands.
That's why these kinds of requests keep
coming in one after another.

\n< Guild Master>And the adventurers who take these
requests are mostly former farmers
themselves.

\n< Guild Master>Those who are just starting out and
desperately need money take these small
jobs to earn a bit of coin.
\n< Serena>Hmmm.

\n< Guild Master>So, it's no job for anyone but former
farmers.

\n< Guild Master>This is probably not a job for you,
young lady.
\n< Serena>That's not necessarily true.

\n< Serena>In my family business. I'm used to
handling livestock.

\n< Serena>Well, I've never touched a cow before,
but if someone teaches me the hand
movements, I'm confident I can manage it
well enough.

\n< Guild Master>Even so... the reward is just 1G, are
you seriously considering taking it?
I'll take it
I won't accept it
請ける

\n< Serena>I'll take it. The reward may be small,
but the evaluation must be high.

\n< Serena>It's the perfect request for me right
now.

\n< Guild Master>...well, even if you fail, it's not like
anyone will die. And all the former
farmers are out anyway.

\n< Guild Master>Better than putting it off till
tomorrow. Here, take this request
certificate with you.

\n< Serena>I just need to show this to the client,
right?

\n< Guild Master>Yeah. The client will be working in the
fields, so show it to them and they
should guide you to the workplace.

\n< Serena>Understood, the fields then. I'll be
going now.
\n< Guild Master>Ah, take care.

\n< Serena>Goblins have appeared again?

\n< Guild Master>They've been quite frequent lately...
Maybe a woman has been captured
somewhere. We've also had some missing
persons here...

\n< Serena>Do goblins increase when a woman is
captured?
\n< Guild Master>Well...
\n< Serena>...

\n< Guild Master>...uh...hmm. Ah...well...you know.
That's how it is.
\n< Serena>???

\n< Guild Master>Anyway, what appeared this time are also
"strays."

\n< Guild Master>They're just a few goblins, but if women
and children encounter them, they could
lose their lives.

\n< Guild Master>It's best to exterminate them quickly.
The reward for success is 3G. Is it okay
to take on this request?
I'll take it
I won't accept it
請ける

\n< Serena>Of course. There's no reason to refuse.
I'll accept that request.
\n< Guild Master>I'm counting on you.

By the way, miss, do you know how to use
items during battle?\n< Guild Master>
I don't know
I know how to
知らない

Alright, then let me give you a quick
lesson.\n< Guild Master>

During battle, you use items from the
slot. If you're using a keyboard, select
with 1 or 2. If you're using a pad,
select with LR and then activate the
item with the slot use button.\n< Guild Master>

There are two slots. You need to
register items to the slots beforehand
through the menu screen.\n< Guild Master>

To do this, go to the slot option in the
menu screen, press the 'register'
button, and just select the item.\n< Guild Master>

Oh, and naturally, you can't register if
you don't have the item in advance.\n< Guild Master>

Items are sold at the tool shop. Make
sure to buy at least one before heading
out on an adventure.\n< Guild Master>

If you skimp because it's expensive, you
might end up paying a much higher price
later.\n< Guild Master>

I've got the gist of it. Thank you,
Master.\n< Serena>
Yeah, make sure to come back safely.\n< Guild Master>
知ってる

Is that so? Looks like you'll be fine
then. Make sure to come back safely.\n< Guild Master>

\n< Guild Master>You don't know the place? It's in the
western direction.
\n< Serena>I understand.
Transporting goods to the Minotaur Forest
ミノタウロスの森への荷物運搬
\n< Serena>...Hmm.
\n< Serena>A Minotaur? This is...

It's a request from Erika. The reward is
1G.\n< Guild Master>

Deliver supplies and a lunch box to the
camp in the forest.\n< Guild Master>

Leaving resupply to someone else? So, is
Lady Erika holed up in the forest?\n< Serena>

...Ricott, her elder sister figure, was
killed by a Minotaur.\n< Guild Master>

She's been searching for her nemesis to
the limits of her strength, occasionally
coming down to town for a brief rest
before heading back to the forest.\n< Guild Master>
There was such a circumstance...\n< Serena>

There's no one without circumstances.
Especially those who are adventurers.\n< Guild Master>
You're the same, aren't you, young lady?\n< Guild Master>
Are you telling me not to pry?\n< Serena>
That's how adult relationships work.\n< Guild Master>
Now, back to the topic at hand.\n< Guild Master>

The job is simply transporting supplies.
There should be hardly any danger.\n< Guild Master>
How much is the cargo?\n< Serena>

Just a small bag. It's mostly just
delivering lunch.\n< Guild Master>

Understood. Then I'll take on the job.
Really, I can't help it.\n< Serena>
Heh...\n< Guild Master>
What is it?\n< Serena>

...It's nothing. Her camp is always in
the same place.\n< Guild Master>

The location is inside the western
forest. I'll attach a map, so follow it
and go there.\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>Noted.

This will be your cargo... I don't worry
about you, but don't handle it too
roughly, okay?\n< Guild Master>
イベント終了
依頼　ミノタウロス捜索終了後

Why don't you play and laugh a little
more? Act like a child while you still
can.\n< Guild Master>

\n< Guild Master>Hey, young lady, there's a message for
you.
\n< Serena>For me?

\n< Guild Master>The woman you saved from the goblins
wants to thank you for that time.
\n< Serena>I see. Tell her not to worry about it.

\n< Guild Master>You're not very gracious. Charm and
amiability are a kid's best assets.
You'll only be doted on while you're
still young, you know?

\n< Serena>Even if you say that... It's just my
nature. And I don't have time.

\n< Serena>More importantly, Master, show me the
requests.

Tough luck, there's no job left that I
can hand over to you right now.\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>What?

In a backwater town like this, there
aren't that many requests to begin with.
It's more common to have days without
work.\n< Guild Master>

Well, it's better than having a mountain
of neglected requests, right?\n< Guild Master>

\n< Serena>That's not good for me. What should I
do?

\n< Guild Master>There's nothing for it but to wait. But
don't worry, you won't be left hanging
for days on end.

\n< Guild Master>We've been having some trouble with a
bandit subjugation request. I was
thinking of sending someone to check on
it soon...
\n< Serena>I wouldn't mind if that were today.

Look, the guild doesn't just issue
requests willy- nilly.\n< Guild Master>

There are budget limits, processing
limits, rules and regulations. We
operate at the edge of efficiency within
those constraints.\n< Guild Master>

Ah, well... Anyway, go home for today.
Or rather, go on. A hardworking young
lady like you needs a break.\n< Guild Master>

...I see... So that's what this is
about. You planned this, didn't you?\n< Serena>
Unnecessary meddling...\n< Serena>

...Well, fine. I've already completed a
task today. And about that woman... I
realize I never asked her name...\n< Serena>

Anyway, it would be a lie to say I
wasn't curious about her.\n< Serena>

Understood. I'll indulge in your
meddling for today.\n< Serena>

But I want you to prepare a request for
me by tomorrow.\n< Serena>
Yeah, yeah, got it.\n< Guild Master>

Her house is on the south side of town.
Take it easy for now.\n< Guild Master>

Honestly... Everyone treats me like a
child and coddles me just because I'm a
bit short.\n< Serena>

\n< Guild Master>The request isn't finished yet. Come
back after you've completed it.

\n< Serena>An Orc? What kind of monster is that?

\n< Guild Master>What do you mean... You don't know what
an Orc is? This is the first time I've
been asked to explain.

\n< Guild Master>Well... Think of them as goblins that
have grown up. They seem to be a
different species though.
\n< Serena>Hmm...

\n< Guild Master>They're muscular and brutally
aggressive. Extremely warlike monsters
that enjoy attacking people.

And it seems an Orc scout has been
lurking around this area. Take it down
before it becomes a serious problem, or
at least drive it away.\n< Guild Master>

\n< Serena>A scout? Does that mean there's a main
force somewhere?

Hard to say. We don't understand the
habits of monsters. But before an Orc
outbreak, there's usually a small group
that appears.\n< Guild Master>

Whether they call for reinforcements or
breed, I don't know, but we refer to
them as scouts anyway.\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>Hmm... Where and how many?

\n< Guild Master>The eastern forest. There are two of
them. For now, they're just wandering
around.

The reward is 1G per Orc, with a success
bonus of 2G. That makes 4G in total. How
about it, will you give it a try?\n< Guild Master>
I'll do it
I won't do it

Yes... I cannot ignore this. I'll accept
the request. However...\n< Serena>
What is it?\n< Guild Master>

If they are as ferocious as you say, I'd
like to do some research on the enemy
first.\n< Serena>

Are there any books or documents
available? Even a report from a previous
encounter would be fine.\n< Serena>

Ah... There aren't any books, but
there's someone in town who knows a lot
about such things.\n< Guild Master>
Oh?\n< Serena>

His name is Toma. Everyone calls him the
Monster Professor, though it's half in
jest.\n< Guild Master>

He's probably the only one in town who
can be said to be knowledgeable about
monsters.\n< Guild Master>
...You seem hesitant.\n< Serena>

...Toma is what you'd call an eccentric.
It's hard to tell what he's thinking
sometimes.\n< Guild Master>

He doesn't seem to be a bad person or a
heretic, but...\n< Guild Master>
A difficult person to deal with, then.\n< Serena>

Yeah. But maybe you'll get along with
him better than most.\n< Guild Master>

What do you mean by that? Well, never
mind. I'll go see him.\n< Serena>

\n< Serena>Poison, huh? This is not a peaceful
request.

\n< Guild Master>Yeah. It's become quite popular lately.
We haven't seen much of it around here
though.
\n< Serena>Poison becoming popular?

\n< Guild Master>You don't know? It's called inheritance
medicine.

\n< Guild Master>Ah, I'm so short on money. If only my
father-in- law would die, I could get
his fortune. Oh, what a coincidence--
\n< Serena>That's enough. So?

\n< Guild Master>There's been a tip-off. Seems there are
people trying to bring it into our town.

\n< Guild Master>It's not fitting for our peaceful town.
I'd like them taken care of.

\n< Guild Master>So this is a request from the guild. Or
rather, from me.

\n< Serena>So I just need to step in and take them
all down?

\n< Guild Master>Yeah, it should be right up your alley.
They're small fry without much backing.
Go ahead and take care of them
thoroughly.

\n< Serena>That's fine, but if they're just small
fry, crushing them will only be a
temporary solution, won't it?

\n< Serena>If we want to stop the influx of poison,
we need to cut off the source.

\n< Guild Master>If that were possible, we wouldn't be
having this trouble. Well, we'll deal
with that gradually.

\n< Guild Master>I'll pay you 4G for this job. Will you
take it?
I'll take it
I won't accept it

\n< Serena>Fine. I'll accept the job.

\n< Guild Master>Thanks. Here's the request form. It also
includes the likely route they'll take.

\n< Guild Master>The location is off the eastern highway.
It's out of sight, so it's perfect for
this kind of thing.

\n< Guild Master>They're not much in number or quality,
but there's always a chance of something
unexpected. Be careful, okay?

\n< Serena>You must judge that I can handle it,
right? Then leave it to me. I'm off.

\n< Serena>Unicorn... Hmm.

\n< Guild Master>What's wrong, young lady? You seem
frozen.

\n< Serena>Th-this request... I'll take on this
request.
\n< Guild Master>Oh, okay.

\n< Serena>Give me the documents. The request

\n< Guild Master>It's rare to see you so flustered...

\n< Guild Master>The client is apparently at the inn, so

\n< Serena>Ah, thank you, Master. I'm off!
\n< Guild Master>Hmm?

第一部最終依頼　導入
Master, this is...\n< Serena>
...\n< Guild Master>
Emergency Rescue Request
緊急救出依頼
Rescue Target: Erika Lindroot
What does this mean?\n< Serena>
Just as you see.\n< Guild Master>

That idiot took on a quest to subdue
bandits, but failed and got captured, it
seems.\n< Guild Master>

The woman Erika saved came to tell us.
Saving this woman was the original
quest, but...\n< Guild Master>

It's no good if you get captured in
exchange...\n< Guild Master>

...Adventurers face such situations.
That's why you prepare by depositing
money with the guild in case you screw
up.\n< Guild Master>

If you don't make it back, you want this
money to be used to issue a rescue
request.\n< Guild Master>

That's why Erika is listed as the client
for this request.\n< Guild Master>

Enough with the preamble. Let me hear
the situation.\n< Serena>
You gonna take it?\n< Guild Master>
Of course.\n< Serena>

This request is different from the
others. It involves humans, and there
are many of them.\n< Guild Master>

Moreover, you have to infiltrate their
stronghold and rescue the hostage. Girl,
you can't do stealth actions, can you?\n< Guild Master>
That's right.\n< Serena>

So, you'll have to fight the bandits
head-on.\n< Guild Master>

They're country bandits. Not very well-
equipped, but still, a group of armed
humans is a terrifying opponent.\n< Guild Master>

Even trained and experienced adventurers
usually avoid fighting.\n< Guild Master>

But Lady Erika went to fight. To save
that woman.\n< Serena>

Yeah, because she's an idiot. To her, it
doesn't matter if she doesn't know the
person's name. I told her to abandon
her.\n< Guild Master>
And you intend to say the same to me?\n< Serena>
...\n< Guild Master>

Don't make that face, Master. The point
is, I just need to be stronger than all
the bandits combined.\n< Serena>
I am confident of that.\n< Serena>
...Has your resolve not changed?\n< Guild Master>

Even if the request can't be accepted
here, I will go on my own.\n< Serena>
Understood.\n< Guild Master>

Then let me formally... ask this of you
as well. Please save her.\n< Guild Master>
Leave it to me.\n< Serena>
I will entrust it to you.\n< Serena>

You'll be infiltrating the bandits'
stronghold. Naturally, you'll have to
deal with them.\n< Guild Master>

But don't go straight in. If it comes to
a fight, Erika will certainly become a
hostage.\n< Guild Master>

Then no matter how strong you are, girl,
you'll be at a loss.\n< Guild Master>

So first secure Erika. Head straight for
her and rescue her.\n< Guild Master>

Then take down the bandits who come at
you. If there's going to be a fight,
that's the order to do it in.\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>That makes sense.

The bandits are using a ruin in the
forest as their base.\n< Guild Master>

An ancient temple or fortress or
something. It's not a very big box
though.\n< Guild Master>

The ruins are built against a sheer
cliff, surrounded by hills, like they're
standing in a depression.\n< Guild Master>
A natural fortress, huh?\n< Serena>

It's not that grand. The slope is gentle
enough to walk up normally.\n< Guild Master>

The reason they're using this as a base
is probably more to do with a desire to
hide away than anything else.\n< Guild Master>

So it's actually convenient for the
invading side?\n< Serena>

Probably. Especially the cliff side,
they're less vigilant. This is according
to Erika's assessment.\n< Guild Master>

Her strategy was to descend quickly
using a rope from the cliff side, then
enter the building from the rooftop and
rescue the hostage.\n< Guild Master>

This rope has pulleys and weights rigged
to it. Light the fuse from below, and
the weight fixed above drops, rapidly
winding up the rope.\n< Guild Master>

After rescuing the hostage, you return
to the rooftop and use this mechanism to
escape quickly. Then you run back to
town.\n< Guild Master>

Despite being able to enter from
anywhere around, she specifically chose
the cliff. It was supposed to catch the
bandits off guard.\n< Guild Master>
But it failed.\n< Serena>
No, she didn't even use it.\n< Guild Master>

It seems she found the woman being taken
outside and spontaneously took her back.
That's according to the woman's story.\n< Guild Master>

It was an unexpected move. Maybe she saw
an opportunity... or simply couldn't
stand by and watch...\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>Erika-sama...

She managed to let the woman escape, but
got caught herself.\n< Guild Master>

But fortunately or unfortunately, the
strategy Erika was supposed to use is
still intact.\n< Guild Master>

She'll be saved by the very plan she
devised herself.\n< Guild Master>

If things go well, we can keep the
battle with the bandits to a minimum.\n< Guild Master>

That's good, but from what I hear, it
sounds like a rather elaborate... in
other words, noticeable setup.\n< Serena>

Isn't there a possibility that after
Erika-sama was captured, the rope was
found and disposed of?\n< Serena>

Ah, of course that's possible. But if
that's the case, then just come back
here.\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>That's true. It was a foolish question.

Then we'll have to rethink our strategy.
But for now, let's proceed as if it's
still there.\n< Guild Master>

The ruins have a three-story structure.
But according to the woman, the first
and third floors are heavily
deteriorated and hardly used.\n< Guild Master>

The bandits' living quarters, storage
for their loot, and the cell where they
keep their captives are all on the
second floor.\n< Guild Master>

Erika is likely being held in a cell on
this second floor. However, even the
woman doesn't know the layout inside the
building.\n< Guild Master>

You'll need to search for where the cell
is once you infiltrate.\n< Guild Master>

Knowing that much is enough. I'll enter
from the rooftop and move through the
uninhabited third floor to find Erika-
sama.\n< Serena>

Yes. But even if you find Erika
successfully, don't rush to her aid
immediately.\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>Why not?

It's a common tactic among bandits. If
they're going to lose a hostage, they
have someone whose role is to kill them
first.\n< Guild Master>
\n< Serena>Despicable...

So find that person first. They'll be
carrying a weapon, so you should be able
to identify them easily.\n< Guild Master>

That's an odd way to put it. Are you
saying the other bandits are "not like
that"?\n< Serena>
Well... probably not.\n< Guild Master>

Thieves, robbers, rapists... since
coming to this town, she's been knocking
down such scoundrels one after another.\n< Guild Master>

There were also a few requests involving
bandits among them. Even though it was
alongside her monster hunting, she must
have caused considerable damage to them.\n< Guild Master>

Having captured Erika, who knows what
those bandits filled with hatred might
be doing to her in their cell...\n< Guild Master>

You mean they might be torturing her to
death...! Damn them...!\n< Serena>

If those bandits had killed Erika, they
would have displayed her body in the
open as a warning.\n< Guild Master>

The fact that they haven't done so means
that, one way or another, she's still
alive.\n< Guild Master>

But we should assume there isn't much
time left.\n< Guild Master>

Time is of the essence. I'll head to the
scene immediately.\n< Serena>
Take this with you as well.\n< Guild Master>

Healing potions, bandages... Ah, all of
these will be necessary for Erika-sama.\n< Serena>

What about this medicine? I've never
seen this bottle before. A skull
mark...?\n< Serena>

That's also for Erika. It's a strong
medicine. Make sure you don't drink it
by mistake.\n< Guild Master>

Something like a stimulant? Understood.
I'll take care of it.\n< Serena>

Yes. That's all I wanted to give you.
The fastest way to the bandit's hideout
is straight through the western forest.\n< Guild Master>

Understood... I promise to bring back
that kind- hearted busybody safe and
sound.\n< Serena>

Miss... I'm counting on you to save
Erika.\n< Guild Master>
第一部最終依頼　導入

If you're heading to the bandit's
hideout, go straight through the western
forest. It's likely to be one battle
after another, so make sure you're well
prepared.\n< Guild Master>

events.note: 依頼の種類とかを教えてくれる

parameters: 序盤依頼三つ進行中

A day laborer's earnings are roughly 1G.
Adventurers risk their lives for an
income of 5 to 10G.\n< Adventurer>

Sometimes I wonder, which one of us is
valuing our own life higher?\n< Adventurer>
ミノタウロスの探索進行中

Transporting supplies, huh? This should
do for today.\n< Adventurer>

Did you know? Adventurers were
originally merchants.\n< Adventurer>

It seems the predecessor to the
Adventurer's Guild was the Trade Guild.
In other words, transportation is the
true calling of an adventurer.\n< Adventurer>
ミノタウロス捜索後

It seems the security in the eastern
town is getting worse every year.\n< Adventurer>

Where people gather, money, disease, and
crime follow.\n< Adventurer>

For the king backing us, as long as the
taxes are paid, I guess nothing else
matters to him.\n< Adventurer>
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中
Hey, you're getting the hang of this.\n< Adventurer>

Working, no matter what it is, is a good
thing. Even the great scholars say so.\n< Adventurer>
依頼三つ終了・フリーモード進行中

The blockade of the bridge is by the
lord's orders. They hastily closed it
off because young folks kept crossing
the river in droves.\n< Adventurer>

Everyone's so eager to go to the city, I
just don't get it.\n< Adventurer>
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始前
Erika-san, are you serious...\n< Adventurer>
Kidnapped by thieves... that means...\n< Adventurer>

Ah, damn it...! But a rescue request is
not something I can...!\n< Adventurer>
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始後

You accepted the rescue request... A
girl like you...\n< Adventurer>
...\n< Adventurer>

events.name: 冒険者女性
events.note: 女性冒険者の心得を教えてくれる

parameters: 序盤依頼三つ進行中
What? Are you lost?\n< Female Adventurer>

There's nothing interesting around here.
Go chase after grasshoppers with your
friends or something.\n< Female Adventurer>
序盤依頼三つ進行中

Goblin extermination? Huh, so you
accepted the quest. You're an adventurer
then...\n< Female Adventurer>

Make sure to take a bath as soon as
you're done. Those guys seriously stink.
Well, I guess that goes without saying,
huh?\n< Female Adventurer>
序盤依頼三つ進行中

Did you see the goblin children? You
made sure to exterminate them, right?\n< Female Adventurer>

After all, the more they live, the more
sin and suffering they bring about.\n< Female Adventurer>

At least disposing of them while they're
young is an act of mercy and virtue.\n< Female Adventurer>
ミノタウロスの探索進行中

Ah, I'm off to run an errand for that
muscle-bound gorilla.\n< Female Adventurer>

Wondering what she's doing holed up in
the forest...\n< Female Adventurer>
ミノタウロス捜索後
"A Minotaur? No, I haven't seen one."\n< Female Adventurer>

"It was supposedly repelled between here
and the forest. I heard it was a close
call, but that's probably an
exaggeration."\n< Female Adventurer>
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

Hey there. Looks like you're getting
used to the adventurer's work, huh?\n< Female Adventurer>
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

Orcs...! Are we really going to fight
them...?\n< Female Adventurer>

They're all muscle-bound and monstrous,
you know? And green. It's just not
natural. I'll pass.\n< Female Adventurer>
At least put on some pants!\n< Female Adventurer>
依頼三つ終了・フリーモード進行中

Haven't you wondered why there are no
gathering requests?\n< Female Adventurer>

It's because I've been taking them all
on. The moment they come up. Instantly.
In seconds.\n< Female Adventurer>

Lately, I've even been stockpiling
various herbs so I can deliver them the
moment I accept the request...!\n< Female Adventurer>
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始前

"Did you hear the Muscle Gorilla got
caught?"\n< Female Adventurer>

"Well, my condolences. Even if he's
alive, he's probably beyond recovery."\n< Female Adventurer>

"That's why we women have to be extra
careful when choosing our quests."\n< Female Adventurer>

"...What's with that look? You know what
happens to women when they get caught,
or what's happening to them. It's not
hard to imagine."\n< Female Adventurer>

events.name: 冒険者男
events.note: 冒険時の注意事項やらを教えてくれる

parameters: 宿を出てから道具屋に行くまで

Make sure to keep items like potions in
an easily accessible place, okay?\n< Adventurer>

If you plan to use them during battle,
make use of the slots. If you don't set
it up before the adventure, you won't be
able to use them when it really matters.\n< Adventurer>
ミノタウロスの探索進行中

In our guild, there was a blonde
adventurer named Ricott. Despite being a
woman, she was incredibly strong.\n< Adventurer>

She went on adventures all over the
place, sort of like business trips, and
became somewhat of a celebrity.\n< Adventurer>

But just the other day, she died
fighting a monster called a Minotaur,
right here in this town.\n< Adventurer>

It makes you wonder what the life of an
adventurer really is. No matter how
strong you are, death can come in an
instant.\n< Adventurer>
ミノタウロス捜索後

Erika and the Master seem to have known
each other for a long time.\n< Adventurer>

They must have some connection through
Ricott. Well, neither of them seems too
keen on talking about Ricott, though.\n< Adventurer>
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

If you're an adventurer, it's natural to
fail sometimes. In fact, failures are
more common than successes.\n< Adventurer>

I've heard that even top-tier
adventurers have a success rate of only
about 60% at best.\n< Adventurer>

For us who are third-rate or lower, it's
of course even worse. That means we have
to think about how to deal with failure.\n< Adventurer>

Even if you fail, life doesn't end. It
won't end for you. Remember that well.\n< Adventurer>
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

Around here, there are still fewer
ferocious monsters. It's thanks to the
river to the east acting as a
breakwater.\n< Adventurer>

Once you cross the river, it's almost
like a different world. The monsters
become more vicious, and the humans who
oppose them become just as brutal.\n< Adventurer>

They say that means there's no shortage
of work, but I prefer a peaceful life of
poverty. It suits me better.\n< Adventurer>
依頼三つ終了・フリーモード進行中

Thieves can generally be categorized
into three types: former mercenaries,
former nobles, and former adventurers.\n< Adventurer>

The thieves around here are mostly
former adventurers. Among them, the
worthless ones who were kicked out of
the eastern river territories.\n< Adventurer>

However, humans become a threat just by
gathering together. The guild around
here can't really handle them.\n< Adventurer>

So we spend our days just waiting,
fingers crossed, for the lord to come
and subdue them.\n< Adventurer>
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始前

It seems being a lord is tough these
days. This thing called money is the
cause of it, they say.\n< Adventurer>

In the past, having a lot of crops was
the lord's power. But money doesn't grow
in rice fields. It's not within the
lord's domain.\n< Adventurer>

The world's rules have changed from
wheat to money.\n< Adventurer>

That's why from now on, nobles won't be
the main characters anymore. Merchants,
cities... it's the era of what you call
the third estate... that's how it is.\n< Adventurer>
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始後
Are you and Erika close?\n< Adventurer>

Then this might be unnecessary advice,
but I'll say it anyway.\n< Adventurer>

Adventurers who can't abandon their
friends don't live long.\n< Adventurer>

It's a saying among us... Ah, I know, I
know. You won't listen anyway.\n< Adventurer>
\n< Serena>I have no business here.
It's a bag.\n< Serena>

It's empty. Money is probably stuffed
into this to give to adventurers as a
reward.\n< Serena>

...Come to think of it, the bag itself
must cost a fair amount.\n< Serena>

Maybe the cost of the bag is deducted
from the reward. Not that it matters to
me.\n< Serena>
It's the request certificate.\n< Serena>

If I take this to the client, it will
serve as proof that I am the contractor
for the request.\n< Serena>

After completing the request, I'll get
the client's signature and bring it
back. It's a completely rational system.\n< Serena>
A scroll... no, it's just paper.\n< Serena>

It seems to be something useful for
writing maps on here. Of course, it's
not free.\n< Serena>
Made of sturdy parchment.\n< Serena>
It's a bag.\n< Serena>

She's taking coins out of it, counting
and looking at them.\n< Serena>
I feel like I shouldn't stare too much.\n< Serena>
It's a request.\n< Serena>
A delivery request to a distant place.\n< Serena>
It's a request that I have no use for.\n< Serena>
It's a request.\n< Serena>
Mercenary recruitment.\n< Serena>

It seems to be about organizing a band
of mercenaries through the Adventurers'
Guild to dispatch to the battlefield.\n< Serena>

In every sense, it's a request that has
nothing to do with me.\n< Serena>
It's a request.\n< Serena>
The subjugation of a bounty head.\n< Serena>

There's no telling how much time the
search will take. I'll pass on this one.\n< Serena>
It's a request.\n< Serena>

Babysitter. Someone with childbirth
experience and a good milk supply.\n< Serena>

Why would such a request be in the
adventurers' guild...? I wonder if
there's someone who will take it. It's
impossible for me, though.\n< Serena>
It's a map.\n< Serena>

It's a rough... really rough map of this
area.\n< Serena>

Detailed maps are confidential for
territorial defense. That's why there's
a demand for such vague maps.\n< Serena>
It's a barrel.\n< Serena>

It moved a bit when I pushed it with my
hand. It seems to be empty inside.\n< Serena>
It's alcohol.\n< Serena>

I don't really like alcohol. It just
makes me feel sick.\n< Serena>

I'm glad I was born in a place with good
water. The water around here is good
too.\n< Serena>
Let's not go behind the counter.\n< Serena>

I don't think I'd get scolded, but it
would surely trouble the master.\n< Serena>
